<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05016f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05016f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05016f"> 16(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Druids buy God</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Being strangers to the bigotry of monotheists, the Philistines <font color="green">[who captured the Jewish Tabernacle]</font> treated old Jahveh with great respect. Although a foreigner, he was still a god, and they were ready to adopt him. Savages often act in that way. Waitz tells us that the Fantees, for instance, even <mark>purchase gods</mark> that have acquired a certain celebrity. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [A God in a Box] 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
